Different educational texts about primary and basic school teachers' profession, preparation, teacher training practice in Estonia and elsewhere, most important issues, strategies (themes chosen by students) in school stages I, II and III are treated. Discussions on educational issues are initiated. Different strategies are used: discussions, case studies, presentations, writing annotations in order to enrich both oral and written expression. Interactive approach and social learning are applied.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To enrich students speciality-related vocabulary and develop their grammar skills (B1 language level) in order to prepare them to work independently with the scientific literature in the field of pre-school and primary school education.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course the student:
knows essential vocabulary in the field of primary school and basic school education and comprehends speciality-related texts (B1language level);
can discuss about educational issues within the range of the vocabulary acquired;
is able to paraphrase and refer to the educational texts;
is able to compile written and oral presentations on the basis of literature in the field of primary school and basic school education.
